**VPS Inspector Professional** adalah tools diagnostik VPS paling komprehensif dengan integrasi AI. Mengumpulkan **150+ metrik** dari 8 kategori, menghasilkan laporan profesional (DOCX/PDF), dan dilengkapi AI untuk error recovery & rekomendasi cerdas.

## 📋 Fitur Utama

| Fitur | Deskripsi |
|-------|-----------|
| 🔍 **System Scanner** | Hostname, OS, kernel, uptime, load average, virtualization |
| 💻 **Hardware Analysis** | CPU model/cores/freq/usage, RAM detail, swap, temperature |
| 💾 **Storage Inspector** | Disk usage, inodes, I/O stats, filesystem types, large files |
| 🌐 **Network Diagnostics** | Interfaces, IP addresses, listening ports, DNS, firewall status |
| 🔒 **Security Audit** | SSH config, failed logins, sudo users, running services, updates |
| 📊 **Performance Metrics** | Top processes, IO wait, context switches, cache efficiency |
| 📦 **Software Inventory** | Nginx, Apache, PHP, MySQL, Node.js, Python, Docker, Redis |
| 📜 **Log Analysis** | Syslog, auth, kernel, nginx, OOM killer, service crashes |
| 🤖 **AI Integration** | 4 NVIDIA AI models, smart error recovery, recommendations |
| 📄 **Professional Reports** | DOCX & PDF output with tables, graphs, executive summary |

## 🚀 Quick Start

### Prerequisites
```bash
# Install Rust
curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh
source ~/.cargo/env

# Install system dependencies (Ubuntu/Debian)
sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y build-essential pkg-config libssl-dev

# For other distros
# RHEL/CentOS: sudo yum groupinstall "Development Tools"
# Arch: sudo pacman -S base-devel openssl
```

Clone & Install

```bash
git clone https://github.com/akaanakbaik/vps-inspec.git
cd vps-inspec
cargo build --release
sudo cp target/release/vps-inspec /usr/local/bin/
```

Run

```bash
vps-inspec
```

Atau langsung dengan Cargo:

```bash
cargo run --release
```

📖 Penggunaan

```bash
# Interactive mode (recommended)
vps-inspec

# Direct scan without prompts
vps-inspec --auto

# Specify output directory
vps-inspec --output /path/to/report

# English language
vps-inspec --lang en

# Bahasa Indonesia
vps-inspec --lang id

# Compare with previous report
vps-inspec --compare /path/to/previous_report.json

# Generate JSON output for automation
vps-inspec --output report.json --format json
```

